Meet <b>Lauren</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Lauren lives at <a href='/home/?user=hi7728'>14996 Bear Mountain View</a>, in the hilltop neighborhood of Westridge. Since moving in on February 14, 2005, she's made a big impression, showing off her talent at everything from sports to Sudoku.<br><br>When asked why she lives in Westridge, she says she wanted her pets to have plenty of space. Plus, the views aren't bad either, and as an animal lover, she loves the horse trails. When she's not breathing in the fresh air atop King's Hill or decorating her house in pink, violet, and green, she rides her skateboard into town and goes to the mall, hangs out at her friends' houses, or joins a pick-up game of basketball! <br><br>But she's not all brawn and no brain &mdash; Lauren's got smarts that keep her grades high. In her spare time, she tutors other students, and she always makes sure to leave time for her best friends. Even though she seems to have it all, this girl is down-to-earth and you can talk to her about anything. So no matter what you want to discuss &mdash; fashion, football, and music are good places to start &mdash; drop in on this cool girl and check out her style (and her yard sale!).<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Lauren, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
